column2: The former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia

column1: a: Not all indicators were available for all countries, so caution should be used in cross-country comparisons. Where an indicator is missing, weights of available indicators are adjusted to total 100 percent. See Technical note 5 at http://hdr.undp.org/sites/default/files/hdr2018_technical_notes.pdf for details.
c:  Missing indicator on child mortality.
d: Child death that occurred anytime was considered, because date of childs death was not collected.
e: Methodology was adjusted to account for missing nutrition and incomplete mortality indicator (date of child's death was not collected).

g: Given the information available in the data, child mortality was constructed using deaths that occurred between survey collections, i.e. between the period 2012-2014. Deaths reported by men were taken into account because there is information about date of death.
h: Missing indicator on cooking fuel.
j: Missing indicator on school attendance.
